{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17414075","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17414075"},"attributes":{"position":31,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T08:38:49+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T08:38:49+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261100"}},"session":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261100"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15594"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17536120","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17536120"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T17:03:46+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T17:03:46+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15594"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261100","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionSessions/1261100"},"attributes":{"startedAt":"2025-09-28T07:52:04+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-28T10:28:52+09:30","sessionType":"qbank","questionStatus":"all","difficulty":[],"timeLimit":null,"questionCount":62,"questionsAnswered":61,"marksTotal":61,"marksAttainable":61,"marksAttempted":61,"finishedAt":"2025-09-28T09:15:31+09:30","resultsAvailable":true,"score":0.2,"questionsCorrect":12,"marksCorrect":12},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"pack":{"data":{"type":"packs","id":"5"}},"exam":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questions","id":"15594","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15594"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.44,0.19,0.29,0.02,0.05]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8285"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"62003"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8285","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8285"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15594"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"47449"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"6"},{"type":"tags","id":"65"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"403"},{"type":"tags","id":"1139"},{"type":"tags","id":"1291"},{"type":"tags","id":"6376"},{"type":"tags","id":"6442"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20005"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"62003","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/62003"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 72-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic for follow-up after a recent hospital admission for severe left-sided pyelonephritis. During her admission, a computed tomography scan showed evidence of pyelonephritis with possible early signs of renal abscess formation. She has just completed an extended course of oral antibiotics. She has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits. There is minimal left flank tenderness on palpation. She reports ongoing mild dysuria. \u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate next step in management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Renal ultrasound","Repeat computed tomography scan","Repeat urine culture","Nuclear medicine renal scan","Magnetic resonance imaging of kidneys"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient requires follow-up imaging after severe pyelonephritis to ensure complete resolution and exclude complications. Given her age, severity of initial infection, and the presence of residual symptoms, structural abnormalities need to be excluded. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERenal ultrasound\u003C/strong\u003E is the most appropriate initial follow-up investigation. It can effectively detect persistent collections, abscesses, hydronephrosis, or structural abnormalities that may have predisposed to the infection. It is readily available, does not involve radiation exposure, and is cost-effective.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERepeat computed tomography\u003C/strong\u003E would involve unnecessary radiation exposure and would be reserved for cases where ultrasound findings are equivocal or if there is clinical deterioration. In cases of confirmed renal abscess, CT would be the imaging modality of choice. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Erepeat urine culture\u003C/strong\u003E alone is insufficient as it would not detect structural complications such as abscess formation or obstruction. While it might be useful to confirm microbiological cure, it should not be the primary follow-up investigation given the severity of the initial presentation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Enuclear medicine renal scan\u003C/strong\u003E would be excessive for initial follow-up. It might be considered later if there are concerns about renal scarring or function, but it is not the most appropriate next step.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMagnetic resonance imaging\u003C/strong\u003E of the kidneys would provide detailed imaging but is unnecessarily complex and expensive for initial follow-up. It would be reserved for cases where other imaging modalities are inconclusive or contraindicated.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Follow-up imaging is essential after severe pyelonephritis to exclude ongoing complications such as abscess or obstruction.","Ultrasound is the preferred initial imaging modality for follow-up of urinary tract infections due to its safety and ability to detect structural abnormalities.","Ongoing symptoms after treatment of pyelonephritis warrant careful evaluation to ensure complete resolution."],"references":["ACR Appropriateness Criteria\u00ae Acute Pyelonephritis: 2022 Update Expert Panel on Urological Imaging. Available online at ; https://www.jacr.org/article/S1546-1440(22)00651-2/fulltext","Demertzis J, Menias CO. State of the art: imaging of renal infections. Emergency radiology. 2007 May;14:13-22. Available online at ; https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Christine-Menias/publication/6488656_State_of_the_art_Imaging_of_renal_infections/links/0fcfd5111015d3f2a1000000/State-of-the-art-Imaging-of-renal-infections.pdf"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"47449"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15594"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"47449","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/47449"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-16T22:59:09+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-16T22:59:10+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8285"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"62003"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"6","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/6"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc75","name":"Geriatrics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"65","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/65"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Investigations","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"72","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/72"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Graduating","synonym